  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Tame the Chaos!\n\nYour Downloads folder has 200+ files — screenshots, PDFs, memes, random ZIPs. Sound familiar?\n\nLet's write a Python script that **automatically organizes files** by their extension into neat folders.\n\n### What You'll Learn\n- Working with `os` and `shutil` modules\n- File path manipulation with `pathlib`\n- Dictionary mapping for file categories\n- Looping through directory contents\n\n### The Plan\n1. Define file categories (images, docs, videos, etc.)\n2. Scan a directory for all files\n3. Create category folders if they don't exist\n4. Move each file to its matching folder\n\n> **Real-world impact:** This script can save you hours every month. Many developers use variations of this daily!"
  },
